RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SALSATION broke in and bumped rival then cleared early, crossed over to the inside on the turn, challenged near the three-sixteenths pole and was overtaken in midstretch, got floated in and bumped late while fighting back and got up at the wire. ELIGIO was off slow to begin, chased at the back early then made some progress four wide around the turn, engaged the leader inside the three-sixteenths pole, inched ahead with a furlong left to run, drifted in and bumped that rival late and was edged on the line. ACE OF CLUBS got bumped from outside by the winner in the beginning, chased two wide into the turn, tried to split rivals on the turn but lost the opening and had to check when PRIME TIME PORTA shifted off the rail, spun four wide into the lane, drifted in through the drive and was along for the show. HALO UNCLE chased the leader from outside to the turn, came three wide into the lane, drifted out a bit then inward in the stretch run and weakened. PRIME TIME PORTA raced up close early from inside, shifted to the two path near the three-eighths pole, and faded in the lane. FOLLOWING AN INQUIRY INTO THE STRETCH RUN, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT SALSATION AND ELIGIO BOTH CONTRIBUTED TO THEIR PROBLEMS AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.OWNER: ERJ Racing LLC Fritz Brothers Racing LLC Pappas Horse Racing Corp and Suarez Pab
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, lost path/checked 3/8,4wide into lane, drifted in

ENTRY.NAME: Salsation
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in/bumped, cleared, floated in/bumped 1/16, dug in

ENTRY.OWNER: Pinkerton Mary Lee and Vetter Michael S
ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, chased 4wide, led 1/8, drifted in/bumped late

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TALKATIVE GAL forwardly placed two wide early, closest in pursuit of the leader up the backstretch, headed that rival at the three-eighths pole and quickly cleared, led two to three wide into the lane and widened under urging. LUCY L chased three wide between before getting put in tight entering the first turn, steered down to the inside around the bend, traveled two then three wide on the far turn, could not threaten the winner in the stretch run but churned on to hold the place. MOVINGLIKEAWINNER bothered by TROJAN WAY soon after the start, trailed three to four wide on the first turn, passed a weakening rival leaving the backstretch, rounded the far turn three then four wide and gained the show. SHVERE ARBETER was off a bit slow and inward to come away last, went up inside to take control then cleared, showed the way to the far turn, overtaken past the three-eighths pole, retreated in the lane and was eased late, then walked off. TROJAN WAY raced up close four then three deep on the clubhouse turn, dropped back off the pace in the middle stages, trailed into and around the far turn off the rail, eased through the lane eventually crossing the wire and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BENEDETTA broke in to bump rival at the start, went between foes to take over and clear early, led off the rail through the turn, coaxed along while the rider took a look back approaching the eighth pole and remained unchallenged by coasting in late. TAMBO stalked four wide into the turn, moved into the three path then came out a bit into the lane, chased after the winner through the lane within striking range but could not summon the needed late kick while clearly second best. RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 95. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Cal-Bred or Cal-Sired horses Allowed a Three (3) Pound Weight Allowance.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIFTH STREET dueled for command around the first turn, lost contact briefly with the leader then went up take control from between rivals at the halfway point, held a short lead while battling through the far turn, dueled outside WORCESTER in the lane, got bumped by that rival at the eight pole then drifted in at the sixteenth pole and dug in to prevail. WORCESTER dueled for command then inched ahead on the clubhouse turn, cleared briefly in the middle stages then got challenged and lost command at the half-mile pole, fought inside foes through the far turn, drifted out and bumped FIFTH STREET at the eighth pole and stayed on gamely to the line. MUCINO got bumped leaving the gate, tracked four wide early, three then four wide on the far turn and held the show. CAPTAIN CHOOCHIES broke a step slow and got bumped at the start, chased two wide then angled out leaving the far turn, moved out further in the lane and improved position. PURE FIRE forwardly placed outside rivals into the first turn, lost touch briefly then bid three deep at the half-mile pole, battled three wide through the far turn and weakened down the lane. FLAT ON took a bump at the start, chased inside early, came two wide into the lane and weakened. HAPPY TEARS was off a bit slow to begin, raced two wide near the back then trailed, saved ground on the far turn and failed to menace. CLASSICALLY bumped inner rival leaving the gate, chased two wide on the first turn, four then five wide on the far turn and weakened. ADVENTURESOME threw his head and came away slow, became rank and altered out into the first turn, went three to four wide on the far turn and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHARLIE'S GHOST got bumped leaving the gate, vied three deep early then dueled outside a rival into the turn, fought four wide into the drive, carried a short lead into the final furlong and drew clear in the final sixteenth. MY BROTHER MIKE vied for the lead between foes early then dueled inside CHARLIE'S GHOST into the turn, rounded the bend two then three wide, fought into the final furlong, yielded to the winner with a sixteenth remaining and saved the place. WE NEED MARKETING vied four deep early then chased the top pair leaving the the backstretch, navigated the turn four then five wide, finished willingly late and missed the place. PAT CAN'T COUNT sat off the pace early on, went two then three wide on the turn, churned on down the lane for a minor award but needed to find more late. LA'OCH ALOYSIUS broke in and bobbled at the start, saved ground in mid-pack on the turn, corned nicely into the lane and lacked a rally. TIGER'S ARROW vied for the lead inside a trio of rivals early then chased the leading pair to the turn, saved ground around the bend and flattened in the furlong grounds. DISTANT STEPPES hit the gate to come away slowly and inward, chased on the inside off the pace, tipped out leaving the bend and lacked a response when called upon. DANZING DREAM shifted in and bumped leaving the gate, began to climb behind rivals early, came four wide into the lane and failed to menace.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Los Alamitos Derby LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 104. Stakes Purse 125000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. By subscription of $100 each to accompany the nomination, or by supplementary nomination of $4,000 each due by closing time of entries. All horses shall pay $1,200 to pass the entry box and $1,200 additional to start, with $125,000 gu aranteed with $75,000 to the winner, $25,000 to second, $15,000 to third, $7,500 to fourth and $2,500 to fifth. Weight 122 lbs. Nominations closed Thursday June 29, 2023, with 12. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. rs to be named through the entry box by the closing time of entries. The Los Alamitos Derby may not be carded with less then five betting interests. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: REINCARNATE stepped to the front early and went two to three wide around the first turn, showed the way up the backstretch, met the bid from PRINCE ABU DHABI on the far turn, maintained a short lead three wide into the lane, kicked clear when asked near three-sixteenths pole and was kept to task to the wire. SKINNER settled in the three path early, moved into range in the middle stages, chased four wide into the lane, got floated out slightly by PRINCE ABU DHABI midstretch, then came in past the eighth pole and finished willingly for the place honors. PRINCE ABU DHABI closest in pursuit from outside into the first turn, chased outside a rival three then four wide around the bend, launched a bid from outside on the far turn, fought four wide into the lane, could not kick on with REINCARNATE in upper stretch, drifted out a bit midstretch then got floated in by SKINNER near the eighth pole and flattened to third. ABELIEFINTHISLIVIN chased behind the leader in the two path around the first turn, traveled along the rail into the second bend, coaxed along two wide into the drive and weakened. SMART MO hopped slightly to come away slow, trailed four wide into the first turn then angled down into the two path, continued two wide into the second bend, was ridden along while easing further off the fence, entered the lane four wide and weakened.
